<subSubSection id="DB687C477313206D78E327820BFFA8EF" pageId="0" pageNumber="64027" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="0277736B177BEA65C49B55D6C5563CC8" pageId="0" pageNumber="64027">Diagnosis</paragraph>
<paragraph id="88697F024C44B35B0D888CD9C072982C" pageId="0" pageNumber="64027">
Male: A medium sized 
<taxonomicName id="3BA61269955ACA1F3DD2BE3E93BE0681" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sphecodes" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="64027" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="204DE4898C7991CFB30CCE5793079993" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="64027">Sphecodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species (6-8 mm) (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="1C59D10F5FE8704EB69D2D1AE8A1DADF" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F6661800" captionText="Figure 5. Sphecodes majalis (Perez, 1903) (Manternach, specimen MNHNL 100057; BOLD identifier MNHNL 163 - 21, one middle leg was used for DNA extraction). a. Dorsal view; b. Lateral view; c. Antenna, showing flagellar segments; d. Left hind tibia, showing spines in pale pubescence; e. Tergites 4 and 5; f. Genitalia. Photos: MNHNL. Background edited using GIMP 2.8.22 (The GIMP Development Team 2020)." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.9.e64027.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/501351" pageId="0" pageNumber="64027">5</figureCitation>
a and b). Flagellar segments of the antenna longer than broad, without pubescence in the front side (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="4097DA1D8C884EEE7B07AC5D03BF60E6" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F6661800" captionText="Figure 5. Sphecodes majalis (Perez, 1903) (Manternach, specimen MNHNL 100057; BOLD identifier MNHNL 163 - 21, one middle leg was used for DNA extraction). a. Dorsal view; b. Lateral view; c. Antenna, showing flagellar segments; d. Left hind tibia, showing spines in pale pubescence; e. Tergites 4 and 5; f. Genitalia. Photos: MNHNL. Background edited using GIMP 2.8.22 (The GIMP Development Team 2020)." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.9.e64027.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/501351" pageId="0" pageNumber="64027">5</figureCitation>
c). The hind tibia present red spines on its upper side amongst a covering of pale hairs (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="7A459E3AA0C5923870F09BDA0C3DDE2B" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F6661800" captionText="Figure 5. Sphecodes majalis (Perez, 1903) (Manternach, specimen MNHNL 100057; BOLD identifier MNHNL 163 - 21, one middle leg was used for DNA extraction). a. Dorsal view; b. Lateral view; c. Antenna, showing flagellar segments; d. Left hind tibia, showing spines in pale pubescence; e. Tergites 4 and 5; f. Genitalia. Photos: MNHNL. Background edited using GIMP 2.8.22 (The GIMP Development Team 2020)." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.9.e64027.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/501351" pageId="0" pageNumber="64027">5</figureCitation>
d). The punctures on tergites 4 and 5 are subtle and very sparsely distributed, presenting fine sculpture amongst them (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E017D523A9CD1905F969C64EED0D2338" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F6661800" captionText="Figure 5. Sphecodes majalis (Perez, 1903) (Manternach, specimen MNHNL 100057; BOLD identifier MNHNL 163 - 21, one middle leg was used for DNA extraction). a. Dorsal view; b. Lateral view; c. Antenna, showing flagellar segments; d. Left hind tibia, showing spines in pale pubescence; e. Tergites 4 and 5; f. Genitalia. Photos: MNHNL. Background edited using GIMP 2.8.22 (The GIMP Development Team 2020)." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.9.e64027.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/501351" pageId="0" pageNumber="64027">5</figureCitation>
e). The gonocoxites lack any impression and the gonostyli have a rounded edge (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B0D255D5D20411DA512773EAF1953A0E" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F6661800" captionText="Figure 5. Sphecodes majalis (Perez, 1903) (Manternach, specimen MNHNL 100057; BOLD identifier MNHNL 163 - 21, one middle leg was used for DNA extraction). a. Dorsal view; b. Lateral view; c. Antenna, showing flagellar segments; d. Left hind tibia, showing spines in pale pubescence; e. Tergites 4 and 5; f. Genitalia. Photos: MNHNL. Background edited using GIMP 2.8.22 (The GIMP Development Team 2020)." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.9.e64027.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/501351" pageId="0" pageNumber="64027">5</figureCitation>
f).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="99F12CDB076EE1C8D4B00AC8B9370459" pageId="0" pageNumber="64027">Voucher specimen (MNHNL100057; BOLD identifier MNHNL163-21): Adult male. Body length of 7.19 mm.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="ACD2742A8DC9A0244909C1E4139FDB82" pageId="0" pageNumber="64027" type="molecular identification">
<paragraph id="74F079DD8789A4F5018D2F96F4476520" pageId="0" pageNumber="64027">Molecular identification</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AFEA5463D96FBB396DC1E1D747E0D599" pageId="0" pageNumber="64027">
The taxonomic annotation is supported by DNA barcoding data. A perfect match of genetic sequence similarity was achieved with a specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="02A162EEB9EBF69DC2C208A3AA88396D" baseAuthorityName="Perez" baseAuthorityYear="1903" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sphecodes majalis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="64027" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="majalis">
<emphasis id="BE557C0AEC6AC388545AFBB05A9F89FF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="64027">Sphecodes majalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from France (100%; BOLD identifier POLLE1165-19), collected in Loir et Cher.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E043EE14DBC6A4B4340E40C70509AF23" pageId="0" pageNumber="64027" type="ecology">
<paragraph id="564713E8CE6AA624AE3565F8906EA527" pageId="0" pageNumber="64027">Ecology</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7314A01C60335F188026B86C05FF64C1" pageId="0" pageNumber="64027">
A rare cuckoo bee that inhabits steppes and sunny sites, flying only during a short time span in spring from late March until mid-May, matching the flight season of 
<taxonomicName id="DD0ADA9BEFED35D37FE83D19539A5190" baseAuthorityName="Brullé" baseAuthorityYear="1832" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Lasioglossum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lasioglossum pallens" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="64027" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallens">
<emphasis id="EE250451F798E553CD35718B53A7A9FB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="64027">Lasioglossum pallens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<normalizedToken id="E8552E6C542899800D7AF7E20ABFC19E" originalValue="Brullé">Brulle</normalizedToken>
, 1832), its only known host in Europe (
<bibRefCitation id="66595CA28381ACBAA6566B2B3C002E62" author="Amiet, F." journalOrPublisher="Fauna Helvetica 20. Apidae 5: Ammobates, Ammobatoides, Anthophora, Biastes, Ceratina, Dasypoda, Epeoloides, Epeolus, Eucera, Macropis, Melecta, Melitta, Nomada, Pasites, Tetralonia, Thyreus, Xylocopa." pageId="0" pageNumber="64027" refId="B6643129" refString="Amiet, F., Herrmann, M., Mueller, A, Neumeyer, R., 2007. . Fauna Helvetica 20. Apidae 5: Ammobates, Ammobatoides, Anthophora, Biastes, Ceratina, Dasypoda, Epeoloides, Epeolus, Eucera, Macropis, Melecta, Melitta, Nomada, Pasites, Tetralonia, Thyreus, Xylocopa. 5" volume="5" year="2007">Amiet et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="9004899A777B8D1A1B7C4BC468BF45E0" author="Bogusch, PETR" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="64027" pagination="1 - 41" refId="B6643137" refString="Bogusch, PETR, Straka, JAKUB, 2012. Review and identification of the cuckoo bees of central Europe (Hymenoptera: Halictidae: Sphecodes). Zootaxa 3311 (1): 1 - 41" title="Review and identification of the cuckoo bees of central Europe (Hymenoptera: Halictidae: Sphecodes)" volume="3311" year="2012">Bogusch and Straka 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="05BBD097790E8BE5BCBFEE9CCCF0D6C6" pageId="0" pageNumber="64027" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="111CD6D0D897DE0A350C663A4D54AD8C" pageId="0" pageNumber="64027">Conservation</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4E51AD4E03B30B216D59438D724E515A" pageId="0" pageNumber="64027">
<taxonomicName id="D08C2BAA9535EC5949FE595A81AEC098" baseAuthorityName="Perez" baseAuthorityYear="1903" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sphecodes majalis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="64027" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="majalis">
<emphasis id="EED987782050A9142037FBB3785A1AC3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="64027">Sphecodes majalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is classified as &quot;Near Threatened (NT)&quot; (
<bibRefCitation id="6EC30E2713A1905014C2B05852F84948" author="Nieto, A." journalOrPublisher="Luxembourg: Publications Office of the European Union" pageId="0" pageNumber="64027" refId="B6643307" refString="Nieto, A., Roberts, S. P.M., Kemp, J., Rasmont, P., Kuhlmann, M., Garcia Criado, M., Biesmeijer, J. C., Bogusch, P., Dathe, H. H., De la Rua, P., De Meulemeester, T., Dehon, M., Dewulf, A., Ortiz-Sanchez, F. J., Lhomme, P., Pauly, A., Potts, S. G., Praz, C., Quaranta, M., Radchenko, V. G., Scheuchl, E., Smit, J., Straka, J., Terzo, M., Tomozii, B., Window, J., Michez, D., 2014. European Red List of bees. Luxembourg: Publications Office of the European Union" title="European Red List of bees" year="2014">Nieto et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
). Records of this bee and its host are scarce and the populations of both are described as locally decreasing (
<bibRefCitation id="253D97642D641326278AD07D1F915226" author="Bogusch, PETR" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="64027" refId="B6643146" refString="Bogusch P. Straka J. Sphecodes majalis. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species 2014 https://www.iucnredlist.org/species/19198950/21148788 2020-12-17T00:00:00+02:00" year="2012">Bogusch and Straka 2014</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
